These are Puzzles for 2x4 Level 8

.:: Puzzle 2x4-Level-8-1::.
There are 4 different favourite colors: lavender, yellow, emerald, fuchsia
4 different pets are kept: ferret, fish, horse, lizard
1. the person who likes emerald is between the owner of the horse and the owner of the fish##2
2. the person who likes fuchsia is on the left or right of the owner of the horse##3
3. the owner of the horse is not to the left of the owner of the horse##8
4. the owner of the fish is not the person who likes emerald##6
5. the person who likes emerald is somewhere to the right of the person who likes lavender##5
6. the person who likes lavender is on the right of the owner of the ferret##1

.:: Answer ::.
|         |    1     |    2    |    3    |   4    |
| Color   | fuchsia  | lavender | emerald | yellow  |
| Pet   | ferret | horse   | lizard  | fish |

 #################################

 
.:: Puzzle 2x4-Level-8-2::.
The people's birthday is in 4 different months: march, february, april, june
House: tower, farmhouse, wooden, modern
1. the modern house is not to the left of the modern house##8
2. the person who's birthday is in march is somewhere to the right of the person who's birthday is in june##5
3. the person who's birthday is in march is the farmhouse house##1
4. the person who's birthday is in june is between the person who's birthday is in march and the person who's birthday is in february##2
5. the person who's birthday is in february is somewhere between the person who's birthday is in april and the tower house##7
6. the wooden house is somewhere to the left of the person who's birthday is in february##5
7. the tower house is not to the left of the tower house##8

.:: Answer ::.
|        |     1      |        2        |    3     |     4      |
| Birthday   | april | february          | june | march     |
| House    | wooden      | modern | tower | farmhouse |

 #################################

 
.:: Puzzle 2x4-Level-8-3::.
House: townhouse, modern, palace, tower
4 different games are played: bridge, go, monopoly, snooker
1. the person playing bridge is not to the left of the palace house##8
2. the person playing go is on the far left##1
3. the modern house is on the right of the townhouse house##1
4. the modern house is in an even position##4
5. the tower house is on the far left or far right##3
6. the townhouse house is somewhere to the left of the person playing snooker##5
7. the tower house is the person playing monopoly##1

.:: Answer ::.
|               |     1     |      2      |     3     |     4     |
| House           | townhouse | modern | palace     | tower |
| Game   | go    | snooker   | bridge | monopoly    |

