.:: Puzzle 2x4-Level-8-7::.
4 different games are played: scrabble, monopoly, mah-jongg, snooker
The people grow 4 different varities of flowers: azalea, iris, orchid, aconite
1. the person who growsiris is not to the left of the person playing monopoly##8
2. the person who growsaconite is somewhere between the person playing snooker and the person who growsorchid##7
3. the person who growsorchid is somewhere to the right of the person who growsazalea##5
4. the person who growsaconite is not to the left of the person who growsazalea##8
5. the person who growsaconite is not to the left of the person playing monopoly##8
6. the person playing scrabble is on the left or right of the person playing mah-jongg##3
7. the person who growsazalea is on the left of the person who growsorchid##1
8. the person playing scrabble is on the left of the person playing snooker##1

.:: Answer ::.
|            |     1     |   2    |      3      |    4    |
| Game   | monopoly      | mah-jongg | scrabble | snooker   |
| Flower      | azalea | orchid | aconite  | iris |

